President Donald Trump and Prime Minister Theresa May held a joint press conference during May's visit to the United States. Trump expressed his honor to have May as the first foreign leader to visit his administration and highlighted the special relationship between the US and UK. He praised the bond between the two countries in military, financial, cultural, and political aspects. Trump also emphasized the importance of government responsiveness to citizens and expressed his support for a free and independent Britain. May, in turn, congratulated Trump on his election victory and emphasized the strength of the special relationship between the US and UK. They discussed topics such as combating terrorism, defense and security cooperation within NATO, and future economic cooperation and trade. May also extended an invitation for Trump and the First Lady to make a state visit to the UK, which he accepted. Both leaders expressed their commitment to working together for the prosperity and security of their respective countries.